data.enText: an object that is used as decoration in a room, garden/yard, etc. rather than for a particular purpose
an object that is worn as jewellery
the use of objects, designs, etc. as decoration

data.chText: 这架时钟纯属摆设，它再也不走了。
data.enText: The clock is simply for ornament; it doesn't work any more.

data.chText: 为…增添光彩的人（或事物）
data.enText: a person or thing whose good qualities improve sth

data.chText: 这座建筑物为整个城市增色不少。
data.enText: The building is an ornament to the city.

data.chText: 雕饰得富丽堂皇的屋子
data.enText: a room richly ornamented with carving

simple_means.memory_skill: orna〔= orn〕装饰；配备 + ment 表名词 → 装饰品

means: 为…增添光彩的人（或事物）

ex.chText: 她的客厅里装点着鲜花。
ex.enText: Her living room is ornamented/decorated with flowers.

ex.chText: 她喜欢那条镶着花边的裙子。
ex.enText: She likes the skirt ornamented/decorated with lace.

synonyms.bx: 通常用于 be ornamented with sth 结构中，指以精美之物美化某处或某物，常可与 decorate 换用。

ex.chText: 她用爱情情节点缀其小说。
ex.enText: She adorned her novel with love affairs.
Her bedroom is adorned with roses.

synonyms.bx: 指以装饰、点缀之物使人、事物、场所等生色，常可与介词 with 连用。

ex.chText: 元旦那天我们教室里装点着鲜花。
ex.enText: Our classroom was decorated with flowers on New Year's Day.

ex.chText: 人们在圣诞节时经常用冬青树枝来装饰房屋。
ex.enText: People often decorate their houses with holly at Christmas.

ex.chText: 他的画把卧室的墙装饰得很好看。
ex.enText: His pictures decorate the walls of the bedroom very well.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，多指对具体场所、事物等进行装饰，使之更加美观，常与介词 with 连用。

tr: make more attractive by adding ornament, colour, etc.
example: Decorate the room for the party
beautify yourself for the special day

value.def: An ornament is an attractive object that you display in your home or in your garden.

example.ex: ...a shelf containing a few photographs and ornaments.
example.tran: 摆放着几张照片和些许装饰品的架子

value.tran: （家中或花园里的）装饰物，装饰品，点缀品

value.def: Pieces of jewellery are sometimes referred to as ornaments .

example.ex: I guessed he was the chief because he wore more gold ornaments than the others.
example.tran: 我估计他是酋长，因为他戴的金饰最多。

value.def: Decorations and patterns on a building or a piece of furniture can be referred to as ornament .
value.tran: （建筑或家具的）装饰物，装饰图案

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to embellish, to equip 装饰；配备
rootsaffixes.title: orn

partsOfSpeech.dec: ad 加强 + orn 装饰；配备 → 装饰
ad 加强 + orn 装饰；配备 + ment 表行为 → 装饰
in 不 + orn 装饰；配备 + ate 具有…的 → 不加修饰的；朴素的
orna〔= orn〕装饰；配备 + ment 表名词 → 装饰品
orn 装饰；配备 + ate 具有…的，有…性质的 → 华丽的；装饰的
sub 下 + orn 装饰；配备 → 在钱的掩饰下让人做坏事 → 唆使
